\- additive partials: prefix a definition with + and multiple declarations
   of the same name merge instead of overwriting.

   the master file has no chapter list. it just references the chapter files
   and renders @toc and @bibliography — both fully populated by chapters
   that registered themselves.

   add a chapter: create the file, add one `reference` line.
   the toc and bibliography grow on their own. -\

reference ./chapters/one.wit
reference ./chapters/two.wit
reference ./chapters/three.wit

@document
@h1 Contents h1@
@toc toc@

@h1 The Book h1@
@chapter_one chapter_one@
@chapter_two chapter_two@
@chapter_three chapter_three@

@h1 Bibliography h1@
@bibliography bibliography@
document@
